  "chapter": {
    "number": 7,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Ephraim’s Iniquity"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "When I heal Israel,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the iniquity of Ephraim",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2479
          },
          {
            "text": "will be exposed,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "as well as the crimes of Samaria.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "For they practice deceit and thieves break in;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "bandits raid in the streets.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "But they fail to consider in their hearts",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "that I remember all their evil.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Now their deeds are all around them;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "they are before My face.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "They delight the king with their evil,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the princes with their lies.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "They are all adulterers,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "like an oven heated by a baker",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "who needs not stoke the fire",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "from the kneading to the rising of the dough.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The princes are inflamed with wine",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "on the day of our king;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "so he joins hands",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "with those who mock him.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For they prepare their heart like an oven",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "while they lie in wait;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "all night their anger smolders;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2480
          },
          {
            "text": "in the morning it blazes like a flaming fire.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "All of them are hot as an oven,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and they devour their rulers.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "All their kings fall;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "not one of them calls upon Me.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Ephraim mixes with the nations;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Ephraim is an unturned cake.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Foreigners consume his strength,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but he does not notice.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Even his hair is streaked with gray,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but he does not know.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Israel’s arrogance testifies against them,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "yet they do not return to the LORD their God;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "despite all this, they do not seek Him.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "So Ephraim has become like a silly, senseless dove—",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "calling out to Egypt, then turning to Assyria.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "As they go, I will spread My net over them;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I will bring them down like birds of the air.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "I will chastise them",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "when I hear them flocking together.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2481
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Woe to them, for they have strayed from Me!",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Destruction to them, for they have rebelled against Me!",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Though I would redeem them,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "they speak lies against Me.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "They do not cry out to Me from their hearts",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "when they wail upon their beds.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "They slash themselves",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2482
          },
          {
            "text": "for grain and new wine,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but turn away from Me.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Although I trained and strengthened their arms,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "they plot evil against Me.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 16,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "They turn, but not to the Most High;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "they are like a faulty bow.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Their leaders will fall by the sword",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "for the cursing of their tongue;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "for this they will be ridiculed",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "in the land of Egypt.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "footnotes": [
      {
